<Layouts.app flash={@flash}>
  <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 mt-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <.custom_nav active="chelekom-docs-navbar" />
    <div class="lg:col-span-10">
      <.custom_info
        title="Navbar"
        description="Navbar components for Phoenix and Phoenix LiveView, featuring responsive navigation bars with customizable styles, logos, menus, and interactive buttons."
        mix="mix mishka.ui.gen.component navbar"
        github="https://github.com/mishka-group/mishka_chelekom/blob/master/priv/components/navbar.eex"
        tags={["Component", "Stateless"]}
      />
      <.custom_tab id="chelekom-navbar-tab">
        <:documentation_panel>
          <.heading2 class="mb-5" id="overview">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/navbar/#overview"}>
              Overview of the Phoenix LiveView Navbar Component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>
          <.cp>
            The
            <strong>
              Mishka Navbar
            </strong>
            component is a <strong>Phoenix LiveView</strong>
            component that enables developers to create fully customizable and responsive navigation bars, perfect for enhancing user engagement. It offers flexible design options, allowing for adjustments in color, layout, and alignment, ensuring a seamless and professional appearance.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper>
            <.navbar id="sample-1" max_width="extra_large" border="border" rounded="rounded-lg">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between w-full">
                <div class="flex-1 md:flex items-center gap-4">
                  <div class="font-bold text-lg">Mishka</div>
                  <ul class="hidden md:flex gap-2">
                    <li class="hover:text-gray-700 dark:hover:text-gray-200 cursor-pointer">
                      Home
                    </li>
                    <li class="hover:text-gray-700 dark:hover:text-gray-200 cursor-pointer">
                      Docs
                    </li>
                    <li class="hover:text-gray-700 dark:hover:text-gray-200 cursor-pointer">
                      Security
                    </li>
                    <li class="hover:text-gray-700 dark:hover:text-gray-200 cursor-pointer">
                      Donate
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="flex-1 hidden sm:flex gap-3 items-center justify-end">
                  <div class="flex items-center flex-nowrap gap-1 w-fit py-0.5 px-2 rounded-md bg-gray-100 dark:bg-[#202022] border border-[#E5E7EB] dark:border-gray-800">
                    <svg
                      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                      width="24"
                      height="24"
                      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                      fill="none"
                      stroke="currentColor"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      class="size-4"
                    >
                      <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8" /><path d="m21 21-4.3-4.3" />
                    </svg>
                    <input
                      disabled
                      class="text-xs appearance-none w-32 bg-transparent border-0 focus:outline-none h-6"
                    />
                  </div>
                  <.avatar size="medium" rounded="full" src={~p"/images/mona-aghili.jpg"} />
                </div>
              </div>
            </.navbar>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.cp margin="mt-5">
            This
            <strong>
              <.link
                title="Phoenix LiveView component"
                class="transition-colors hover:text-[#448D96]"
                navigate={~p"/chelekom"}
              >
                Phoenix LiveView component
              </.link>
            </strong>
            supports multiple design variants such as default, shadow, and bordered, making it ideal for improving both the aesthetic and functionality of your application's navigation. With its responsive design and ease of customization, this navbar component enhances the usability and accessibility of your website's interface.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_block position="left" color="success" class="my-8" border="medium">
            <.cp>
              By using the class prop, you can apply custom classes or
              <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong>
              classes to customize the appearance and behavior of the gallery, allowing for flexible design changes.
            </.cp>
          </.custom_block>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="base-navbar">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/navbar/#base-navbar"}>
              Base Color & Variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-5" code={@code_18}>
            <.navbar id="navbar-example-13333" max_width="extra_large">
              <:start_content>
                <.link
                  navigate={~p"/"}
                  class="flex items-center space-x-3 rtl:space-x-reverse mb-5 md:mb-0"
                >
                  <img src={~p"/images/mishka-logo-white.svg"} class="hidden dark:block size-10" />
                  <img src={~p"/images/mishka-logo.svg"} class="dark:hidden size-10" />
                  <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold">
                    Mishka
                  </h1>
                </.link>
              </:start_content>
              <:list><.link title="Mishak" navigate="/">Mishka</.link></:list>

              <:list><.link title="Mishak chelekom" navigate="/chelekom">Chelekom</.link></:list>

              <:list><.link title="Mishak blog" navigate="/blog">Blog</.link></:list>

              <:list><.link navigate="/chelekom/docs">Docs</.link></:list>
            </.navbar>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="default-variant-navbar">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/navbar/#default-variant-navbar"}>
              Default Variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The default style of the
            <.link navigate={~p"/chelekom/docs/navbar"}>Mishka Chelekom navbar</.link>
            applies a solid background and border that change based on user interaction, making it perfect for delivering important notifications. With just a single setting, you can select from a range of color options, ensuring easy customization to match various design styles. Default variant have also white and dark colors which are the same colors in the dark and light mode.
          </.cp>

